Thorntons Sales for Two Months to June 25 Fall 8.4%

-- B y   K i r a   S a v c e n k o
-- 
2011-07-13T15:44:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/thorntons-sales-for-two-months-to-june-25-fall-8-4-1-.html
Thorntons Plc (THT) , the U.K.
confectionery-maker that plans to close at least 120 stores,
said total sales for the eight weeks to June 25 fell 8.4 percent
to 20.6 million pounds ($32.9 million).  Sales in the year to that date rose 1.7 percent to 218.3
million pounds, the Alfreton, Central England-based company said
today in a Regulatory News Service statement .  Thorntons own-store fourth-quarter sale fell 11.9 percent
to 12.8 million pounds, while franchise sales declined 19
percent to 1.1 million pounds.  Thorntons said on June 28 it plans to make the store
closures over the next three years, with the possibility of an
additional 60 closures. It will leave the confectionery-maker
with around 180 to 200 company-owned stores nationwide.  The companyâ€™s shares fell 2.6 percent to 54.3 pence at the
4:30 p.m. close in  London . The stock has fallen 45 percent in
the year, giving a market value of 37.1 million pounds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
